Steps to compile tensorflow for use with ROS:
 * install Bazel (v0.15.0)
   https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/releases/download/0.15.0/bazel-0.15.0-dist.zip
 * git clone https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow.git
 * cd tensorflow
 * git checkout v1.12.0
 * ./configure
 * bazel build -c opt --config=monolithic //tensorflow:libtensorflow_cc.so (refer to https://medium.com/@tomdeore/standalone-c-build-tensorflow-opencv-6dc9d8a1412d)
 * copy the library files to a lib directory:
    mkdir ../my_proj/lib
    cp bazel-bin/tensorflow/libtensorflow_cc.so ../my_proj/lib/
    cp bazel-bin/tensorflow/libtensorflow_framework.so ../my_proj/lib/
 * copy the include files:
    cp -r bazel-genfiles/* /home/jseng/catkin_ws/image_test/include/
    cp -r tensorflow/cc /home/jseng/catkin_ws/image_test/include/tensorflow
    cp -r tensorflow/core /home/jseng/catkin_ws/image_test/include/tensorflow
    cp -r third_party /home/jseng/catkin_ws/image_test/include/
